title: rounded typeface...
content:
Can any of you guys help me out with identifying this rounded typeface PLEASE...?

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20090629040014im_/http:/typophile.com/files/typeface1_3636.jpg)

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20090629040014im_/http:/typophile.com/files/Typeface2_4368.jpg)
author: bigbird

comments.content: Quick guess is that it was a custom typeface done by a design firm, not a type designer. Lots of beginner mistakes in there. Recommended alternatives: [FF Netto](http://web.archive.org/web/20090629040014/http:/www.fontshop.com/fonts/downloads/fontfont/ff_netto_ot/), [Chevin](http://web.archive.org/web/20090629040014/http:/www.fontshop.com/fonts/downloads/gtype/chevin/), [Gravur Condensed](http://web.archive.org/web/20090629040014/http:/lineto.com/The+Fonts/Font+Categories/Text+Fonts/Gravur+Condensed/).
Cheers Stephen - a couple of those alternatives should do nicely.
To add to Stephen’s list, Router is another option — and it has bulbous terminals that are reminiscent of your sample’s.
